About this Item

Photographie,Frederick VIII (Christian Frederik Vilhelm Carl) (3 June 1843 ? 14 May 1912) was King of Denmark from 1906 to 1912. Before his accession to the throne at age 62, he served as crown prince for 43 years. During the long reign of his father, King Christian IX, he was largely excluded from influence and political power. // Circa 1894 // Tirage citrate // Format (cm): 10x15. Seller Inventory # CS6784
